  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures: it parameterizes neuron-selection with 29 interpretable neuron features, records which feature-weighted strategies produce coverage/adversarial inputs, and empirically analyzes the learned feature weights and coverage-vs-defect correlations (Sections 3.1, 3.2, 4.3, 4.4). These analyses provide partial diagnostic insight tied to model internals (which neurons/layers or activation patterns are associated with effective testing and with finding misclassifications). However, the paper does not trace failures to deeper root causes such as corrupted or biased training data, spurious input features, or overfitting of the training process, nor does it propose mitigations that directly address such root causes. Therefore the diagnostic content is substantial but limited to characterization via model internals and observed failure patterns, matching the metric's description of a 'Medium' rating.",
